author: Ryan Schwartz
excerpt: On TV this Week: 'Love Is Blind,' 'The Masked Singer' and 'Yellowjackets' return with new seasons, while 'Cobra Kai' comes to an end.
text: This weekly feature is in addition to TVLine’s daily What to Watch column, our monthly breakdown of What’s on Streaming, and our master list of Every New TV Show Premiering in 2025. With over 500 scripted shows now airing across broadcast, cable and streaming, it’s easy to forget that a favorite comedy is returning, or that the new “prestige drama” you anticipated is about to debut. So consider this our reminder to set your DVR, order a Season Pass, pop a fresh Memorex into the VCR… however it is you roll. This week, you’ll find 10 returning series (including Love Is Blind, The Masked Singer and Yellowjackets), six finales (including Dexter: Original Sin, High Potential and the very last episode of Cobra Kai) and a little known sporting event known as the Super Bowl. html:
This weekly feature is in addition to TVLine’s daily What to Watch column, our monthly breakdown of What’s on Streaming, and our master list of Every New TV Show Premiering in 2025.

With over 500 scripted shows now airing across broadcast, cable and streaming, it’s easy to forget that a favorite comedy is returning, or that the new “prestige drama” you anticipated is about to debut. So consider this our reminder to set your DVR, order a Season Pass, pop a fresh Memorex into the VCR… however it is you roll.

This week, you’ll find 10 returning series (including Love Is Blind, The Masked Singer and Yellowjackets), six finales (including Dexter: Original Sin, High Potential and the very last episode of Cobra Kai) and a little known sporting event known as the Super Bowl.

SUNDAY, FEB. 9
12 pm Great American Rescue Bowl (Great American Family)
2 pm Puppy Bowl (Animal Planet, Discovery Channel, Discovery+, Max, TBS & truTV)
6:30 pm Super Bowl (Fox & Tubi)
10:30 pm The Floor Season 3 premiere (Fox)

MONDAY, FEB. 10
3 am Surviving Black Hawk Down docuseries premiere (Netflix; all three episodes)
8 pm All American Episode 2/time slot premiere (The CW)
8 pm Extracted series premiere (Fox)
10 pm The Hunting Party Episode 2/time slot premiere (NBC)

TUESDAY, FEB. 11
3 am Muslim Matchmaker series premiere (Hulu; all eight episodes)
3 am The Witcher: Sirens of the Deep movie premiere (Netflix)
9 pm High Potential Season 1 finale (ABC)

WEDNESDAY, FEB. 12
3 am Are You Smarter Than a Celebrity? Season 1 finale (Prime Video)

3 am Harlem Ice docuseries premiere (Disney+; all five episodes)
8 pm The Masked Singer Season 13 premiere (Fox)
9 pm The Floor Episode 2/time slot premiere (Fox)
9 pm Inside the NFL Season 47 finale (The CW)
9 pm Summer House Season 9 premiere (Bravo)

THURSDAY, FEB. 13
3 am Beast Games Season 1 finale (Prime Video)
3 am Bridget Jones: Mad About the Boy movie premiere (Peacock)
3 am Cobra Kai Season 6, Part 3 premiere (Netflix; last five episodes)
3 am La Dolce Villa movie premiere (Netflix)
3 am Sly Lives! (AKA The Burden of Black Genius) documentary premiere (Hulu)
8 pm Next Level Chef Season 4 premiere (Fox)
9 pm C.B. Strike Season 6 (aka The Black Ink Heart) finale (HBO)

FRIDAY, FEB. 14
3 am Dexter: Original Sin Season 1 finale (Paramount+ With Showtime)
3 am Goldie series premiere (Apple TV+; all 13 episodes)
3 am The Gorge movie premiere (Apple TV+)
3 am Love Is Blind Season 8 premiere (Netflix; first six episodes)
3 am Waitress: The Musical streaming premiere (Max)
3 am Yellowjackets Season 3 premiere (Paramount+ With Showtime; first two episodes)
7 pm NBA All-Star Celebrity Game (ESPN)
8 pm NBA Rising Stars (TNT & truTV)

SATURDAY, FEB. 15
6 pm WWE Vengeance Day (Peacock)
8 pm NBA All-Star Saturday Night (TNT)
9 pm Have I Got News for You Season 2 premiere (CNN)
